    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-04T09:02:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-04T09:02:00-05:00" n="899"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d899">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795B.5/6–354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d899fn1">This telegram, drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRJG1">McClurkin</persName> and cleared by Drumright, was
                        repeated to Tokyo as telegram 2688 and to Geneva as telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 342.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>limit distribution</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-04T10:02:00-04:00"
                            >June 4, 1954—10:02 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>984. Seoul’s 1292<note n="2" xml:id="d899fn2">Not printed, but see <ref
                            target="#d898fn1">footnote 1</ref>, <hi rend="italic">
                            <ref target="#d899">supra</ref>
                        </hi>.</note> repeated Tokyo 769 Geneva 151. Regret following information
                    not provided earlier messages this subject.</p>
                <p>We will be glad exchange ratifications and bring unchanged Treaty into effect at
                    any time but do not wish urge it upon <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> now
                    that we have made offer and any delay is their responsibility.</p>
                <p>Do not believe August 8 agreed statement need be considered in this connection.
                    It reads “between now and date when Mutual Defense Treaty <hi rend="italic">can
                        be expected to</hi> come into force and effect” <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                        >ROK</gloss> armed forces will be subject to <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                        >UNC</gloss>. That commitment ran out about end of March. Later paragraph in
                    August 8 agreed statement says <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> “has agreed
                    take no unilateral action unite Korea by military means for agreed duration
                    political conference”. Presumably that commitment runs out when conference ends.
                    However whether or not there exists explicit commitment retain <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> forces under <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                        >UNC</gloss> we believe factors mentioned second and third paragraphs your
                        1259<note n="3" xml:id="d899fn3">Dated May 28, <ref target="#pg_1800">p.
                            1800</ref>.</note> operate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
